Whenever you make changes to the codebase, you must automatically create a commit summarizing the changes and push them to the current GitHub repository. Ensure that the commit message accurately describes what was changed.

Additionally, ensure that you save summary logs of all conversations with the user to the `conversations.md` file in the root directory.

Always use the virtual environment (`venv`) when running commands or installing dependencies. 
Ensure the code is well-documented; always write clear comments explaining the logic for all files, functions, and complex logic.
